content.description: 135'!  Rap fall guy with a 70M rope to approach or slog from below, tough to rap to the start from it's anchor because of the diagonal nature and sketchy slab landing.  Starts at Fall Guy and trends diagonally right up a low angle hand corner crack that is rudely interrupted by a steep very awkward thin hands to slot crux over a nasty ledge.
content.protection: Many hand sized cams with a red and a 3.5 camalot sized piece.

content.description: 125'!  Identified by a dark varnished wide hands corner.  (a little beyond the awesome looking varnished finger crack corner) A 70M rope barely reaches the base.  Scamper up the right side of the big flake to the base of the corner.  Climb the slippery but fun V chimney past a bolt until you can reach the steep big hands corner.  Tape gloves recommended for some sharp calcite near the top.  Notice the fingers crack to undercling roof to fingers corner a little ways right
content.protection: A couple red and gold camalots and 4-5 blue camalots, possibly a 1 cam for the top.  Runners help with rope drag.

content.description: 125'!  A fun varied crack in a shallow corner. Dont expect to slide a cam with you on this one.  Real trad climbing.
content.protection: Eats a double rack from small to #4 camalots and some medium  large nuts.
content.location: (Climbers) left of 2 cracks next to each other not far beyond the Gauntlet Wall.  Rap in with a 70M rope or slog in from below.
